---
description: Formatting rules for all markdown docs. Optimizes for editor readability, not preview mode.
alwaysApply: true
---

User reads markdown in the editor, not preview. Everything must be scannable as raw text.

Do:
- Short paragraphs (2-4 sentences)
- Bullet lists for discrete items
- Numbered lists when order or reference matters
- Bold for key terms inline
- `- [ ]` checkboxes when tracking completion
- Blank lines between sections
- `##` / `###` headers to break up content
- Links inline where they naturally fit

Do not:
- Markdown tables — unreadable without preview. Use prose with bold labels or lists. No exceptions.
- Excessive bold/italic
- Deeply nested bullets (2 levels max)
- Long unbroken paragraphs
- Emoji unless asked
- Repeating same info in different formats
- Inline HTML
- `####` or deeper headers — restructure instead
- Hard line wraps at 80 chars — let editor handle it
